annotationA: Triose phosphate isomerase is a soluble metabolic protein dimer that functions in glycolysis catalyzing the isomerization between dihydroxyacetone phosphate and glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate, which is essential for efficient ATP production
annotationB: CG7362; Potassium ion binding; magnesium ion binding; pyruvate kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: phagocytosis; glycolytic process
